org.dspace.foresite

Interface OREResource

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Agent, AggregatedResource, Aggregation, Proxy, ResourceMap
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AgentJena, AggregatedResourceJena, AggregationJena, OREResourceJena, ProxyJena, ResourceMapJena

    public interface OREResource
    Interface for every ORE Resource that will be implemented. This is, in turn, extended by every explicit resource type interface. This interface defines general RDF graph methods that we will want to perform on individual resources and the graphs of which they are members, as well as common ORE operations which apply to each resource
    Author:
    Richard Jones
    See Also:
    Agent, AggregatedResource, Aggregation, Proxy, ResourceMap

      • removeTriple

        void removeTriple(Triple triple)
           throws OREException
        Remove the given triple from the current graph. Removal of the triple should not result in the graph becoming unconnected. If it does, all relationships to the left of the triple (i.e. those referring to the object of this triple) will be removed (recursively).

        triple -
        Throws:

      • empty

        void empty()
    throws OREException
        Remove everyting inside the object, but leave the object itself in existence. This removes everything as follows:
        • All triples with the ORE resource as the subject
        • All triples which are descended from the ORE resource by hierarchy
        • All resources which are no longer connected in the graph once the two above removals have completed
        Throws:
        OREException

      • detach

        void detach()
     throws OREException
        Detach the current object from the current model. This will not affect the object in the model, but will create a new copy which contains only the following:
        • All triples with the ORE resource as the subject
        • All triples which are descended from the ORE resource by hierarchy (except as described by the list below)
        It WILL NOT contain the following:
        • Other ORE Resource descriptions
        Throws:
        OREException
